Generals,

Our school district has requested a Needs Assessment Survey conducted by the Iowa Association of School Boards (IASB). The survey is designed to help us assess our strengths and areas of needed improvement, with a focus on improved student achievement. We would like your opinions and judgments in response to the brief survey linked below. The survey takes an average of 9 minutes to complete. All responses are anonymous.

Just click the link below, or paste it in your browser and follow the instructions. Thank you for your participation and helping to make improvements for our students. Please reply with any questions.

Today is the day! We are excited that tonight is the Pork Chop Supper fundraiser at the home high school football game! GO GENERALS!
All the food will be purchased outside the east gate of the football field near the skate park. The food will be packaged to-go and there will be no seating due to COVID-19 precautions. All members and parents working will be wearing masks and gloves as well.
A Pork Chop dinner with a drink (lemonade, tea or water), potato, roll and applesauce will be $10. A Hot Dog dinner with a drink, chips and applesauce will be $5.
The proceeds of this fundraiser will go towards purchasing FFA jackets for our new S-O FFA members! Thanks for your support!

We are looking for students who would like to get some volunteer hours and help our school out. We have over 2 large tables of trophies that need to be sorted and cataloged. Please contact the HS office if you are interested.

Thanks

BASEBALL/SOFTBALL GAME INFORMATION FOR SPECTATORS

Fans, in cooperation with Osceola County and the Iowa Department of Public Health, we ask that you follow social distancing guidelines and sit six-feet apart from other spectators outside of your immediate household.

We ask all spectators and guests to follow all seating protocols set in place by our school and administrators for your safety. Please refrain from sitting in restricted areas.

Should a ball go out of play we ask you to please refrain from picking it up.

Fans and participants, a reminder to please refrain from spitting and no spitting sunflower seeds on the premises.

All coolers are subject for inspection per on-site administrator.

THANK YOU FOR YOUR COOPERATION - YOUR EFFORTS WILL ENSURE THE CONTINUATION OF CONTESTS AND THE ABILITY FOR SPECTATORS TO ATTEND!

post_text: Just in time for Memorial Day, our new flagpole at the high school was installed today. The former pole was bent and difficult to operate, and the flag could not be displayed after hours because there wasn‚Äôt a light on it. Now the pole has steel cables on the inside, a solar light, and a free-spinning attachment so the flag will not get tangled up. The pole is appropriate size for the building, and the flag is also the correct size for the height of pole. We are proud to be able to display our flag with the new pole and remember all who sacrificed for our country this Memorial Day and every day!
text: Just in time for Memorial Day, our new flagpole at the high school was installed today. The former pole was bent and difficult to operate, and the flag could not be displayed after hours because there wasn‚Äôt a light on it. Now the pole has steel cables on the inside, a solar light, and a free-spinning attachment so the flag will not get tangled up. The pole is appropriate size for the building, and the flag is also the correct size for the height of pole. We are proud to be able to display our flag with the new pole and remember all who sacrificed for our country this Memorial Day and every day!

Graduation/Commencement Weekend.

Just a reminder of the events to honor our S-O Graduating Class of 2020 this weekend.

Friday, May 15th - Starting at 5 pm - Our Retiree and Graduate Parade through both Sibley and Ocheyedan. See pictures for actual routes. We would love to see the route lined with people, socially spaced, cheering them on!

Sunday, May 17 - Starting at 2 pm - Commencement ceremony (graduates and family only). The event will be broadcast on 104.3 and will also be made available for live and future viewing on the district's Youtube channel. Watch Social Media for when the link is made available.

GO GENERALS!!

post_text:
Two S-O performers chosen as Individual Events All-State speech performers

Two Sibley-Ocheyedan speech contest students have received the highest honor by the Iowa High School Speech Association by receiving All-State performer nominations from their three-judge panel following the virtual state contest held on Saturday, May 9, 2020.

Nominated performers are Timothy Jenson ‚Äì After Dinner Speaking, ‚ÄúHave a Very Dairy Day‚Äù; and Eric Jungers ‚Äì Interpretation of Prose, ‚ÄúThe Secret to a Long Life‚Äù.

Nominees will receive recognition for this honor locally, as well as from the state speech office in Des Moines in the form of certificates and medallions at a later date.

The Sibley-Ocheyedan speech squad is coached by head coach B.J. Schuller, and assistant coach Rachel Keber.

post_text:
State Large Group Speech Results
On Saturday, February 8, 2020, the Sibley-Ocheyedan large group speech team competed at the state speech contest in LeMars. Eleven contestants participated in two entries in the competition. One of these entries received a ‚Äú1‚Äù rating (excellent) overall from their judges, while the other entry received a ‚Äú2‚Äù rating (good).

The group receiving the cumulative 1 rating was: Ensemble Acting ‚Äì ‚ÄúBest Seller?‚Äù ‚Äì Morgan Gleason, Dimitri Lobo and Tori Vande Hoef.

The group receiving a 2 rating was: Reader‚Äôs Theater ‚Äì ‚ÄúThe Empty Chair‚Äù - Rylie Boer, Jaydee Bremer, Morgan Huls, Tyra Jansma, Andrea Leusink, Nick Ruete, Tavian Plotz and Jillian Van Diepen.

Congratulations to all large group speech participants for their efforts and for sharing their talents with northwest Iowa throughout this Large Group season.

One of these entries received a ‚Äú1‚Äù rating (excellent) overall from their judges, while the other entry received a ‚Äú2‚Äù rating (good).

The group receiving the cumulative 1 rating was: Ensemble Acting ‚Äì ‚ÄúBest Seller?‚Äù ‚Äì Morgan Gleason, Dimitri Lobo and Tori Vande Hoef.

The group receiving a 2 rating was: Reader‚Äôs Theater ‚Äì ‚ÄúThe Empty Chair‚Äù - Rylie Boer, Jaydee Bremer, Morgan Huls, Tyra Jansma, Andrea Leusink, Nick Ruete, Tavian Plotz and Jillian Van Diepen.

Congratulations to all large group speech participants for their efforts and for sharing their talents with northwest Iowa throughout this Large Group season.

post_text: It‚Äôs Election Day! The polls are open and you are encouraged to get out and vote - for school board District 5 has two candidates: Kristin Beyer and Roxanne Hayenga. Board president Kyle Grimes is running in District 2. These are at-large elections, so the races are all on the same ballot and all eligible voters, regardless of district, can vote in both district races. Let your voice be heard and exercise your right to vote!
text: It‚Äôs Election Day! The polls are open and you are encouraged to get out and vote - for school board District 5 has two candidates: Kristin Beyer and Roxanne Hayenga. Board president Kyle Grimes is running in District 2. These are at-large elections, so the races are all on the same ballot and all eligible voters, regardless of district, can vote in both district races. Let your voice be heard and exercise your right to vote!
